    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong>, <strong>drained chickpeas </strong>and <strong>chopped potato </strong>to the pot<strong> </strong>with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15-18 min or until the potato is tender and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>smoky bacon & chickpea stew</strong></p>",
